    <div class="content-wrapper">

      <div class="box">
        <h1>Health &amp; Social Care</h1>
        <p>
          The Health &amp; Social Care pathway at Specialist Technical College provides
          a foundation in the knowledge, skills and values required for work in care,
          support and related sectors. It is informed by British vocational practice
          and adapted to the local context in Kosovo.
        </p>
        <p>
          Learners explore key themes such as communication, safeguarding, person-centred
          practice and professional responsibilities, preparing them for further study
          or entry-level roles under supervision.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>Core Areas of Study</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Human growth, development and wellbeing</li>
          <li>Communication in health and social care settings</li>
          <li>Values, ethics and person-centred approaches</li>
          <li>Introduction to safeguarding and duty of care</li>
          <li>Working with individuals, families and communities</li>
          <li>Record keeping and reflective practice</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>Learning and Assessment</h2>
        <p>
          Teaching is delivered through classroom sessions, case studies,
          group work and guided independent learning. Assessment commonly
          includes written assignments, presentations and scenario-based tasks,
          reflecting British vocational approaches.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>Progression Opportunities</h2>
        <p>
          Health &amp; Social Care study can support progression to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Further or higher-level study in health, social care or related areas.</li>
          <li>Entry-level roles in care settings under appropriate supervision.</li>
          <li>Complementary professional development for those already working in the sector.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Applicants are encouraged to discuss their goals with the college so that
          an appropriate study pathway can be identified.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2>Further Information</h2>
        <p>
          For detailed information about units, timetables and entry requirements
          for Health &amp; Social Care, please contact:
        </p>
        <p>
          Email: <a href="mailto:info@specialist.college">info@specialist.college</a>
        </p>
